            . I am an officer. I was sent for, and took the prisoner - he took me to the pawnbroker's.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290910-310-person2909">
                  REBECCA 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18290910-310-person2909" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-310-person2909" type="given" value="REBECCA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-310-person2909" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . These articles are my property; I am quite sure my window was shut down - I thought it would not open without breaking, but it did, and he had broken a knife in opening the drawers.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence (written.) I have never before, on any occasion, been accused of an offence against the laws of my country, but have lived with my parents, and have at all times maintained a good character with those who knew me. This act I was tempted to commit, at the request of 
               <persName id="t18290910-310-person2910">
                  William 
                  Budd
               <interp inst="t18290910-310-person2910" type="surname" value="Budd"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-310-person2910" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-310-person2910" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who opened the window of the house, and asked me to get in, and told me what to do; when I came out he took the bundle and went away with it; afterwards sharing the 10s. This statement is not made with a view of exeulpating myself, by implicating him, but to shew the Court, that although I am guilty of an offence, the commission of it was not contemplated or planned, but accidental, in consequence of meeting with William Budd.</p>
               <p>Three witnesses gave the prisoner a good character.</p>
               <p>GUILTY - <rs id="t18290910-310-punish1713" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290910-310-punish1713" type="punishmentCategory" value="death"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290910-310-defend2901 t18290910-310-punish1713"></join>
               DEATH
            </rs> Aged 13.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18290910-310-verdict1714" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290910-310-verdict1714" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-310-verdict1714" type="verdictSubcategory" value="withRecommendation"></interp>
               Recommended to Mercy by the Jury, on account of his character and youth, and believing him to be seduced by Budd
            </rs>.</p>
